## 4️⃣ Suggested folder structure (clean & scalable)

```text
notification/
├── orchestrators/
│   └── notification.orchestrator.ts
│
├── services/
│   ├── notification.service.ts
│   ├── notificationLog.service.ts
│
├── delivery/
│   ├── notification.dispatcher.ts   // decides sync vs async
│
├── queues/
│   └── notification.queue.ts        // BullMQ only
│
├── workers/
│   └── notification.worker.ts       // FCM / email logic
│
├── types/
│   └── notification.type.ts
```

### Why this works in production

- Queue logic is isolated
- Workers don’t touch DB creation
- Orchestrator doesn’t know FCM details

